Class HeapPriorityQueue<K,E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • classes.HeapPriorityQueue<K,E>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - a Key
    E - an Element
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    BasicCollection<E>, PriorityQueue<K,E>

    public class HeapPriorityQueue<K,E>
extends java.lang.Object
implements PriorityQueue<K,E>
    This Class HeapPriorityQueue implements a Priority Queue based on a Heap and its comparators. * since 1.1 - overall generic types used (Hint: Haenni) since 1.2 - using LinkedList datastructure instead of ArrayList since 1.3 - implemented Item and ItemComparator for making Map and LinkedList obsolete
    Version:
    1.3
    Author:
    mosea3@bfh.ch
